The truth is.. I’ve hated this fridge for the 7 years since we’ve had this house 🥲. Side-by-side fridges are my least favorite fridge layout, because both the freezer and the fridge compartments are extremely narrow, yet deep. Thus, everything gets lost in the Narnia depths in the back of the fridge. 😭 Because of my hatred for this fridge, I refused to buy the nicer organizers which would (and have) ultimately made my life easier. I probably would have saved a ton of money because food always got lost and went bad. Recently, I decided to change my outlook, because this fridge has been good to us and she still (mostly) works fine. I measured all of the areas meticulously and even made a written diagram of how I would store everything. Then I set out to find the right organizers to fit the dimensions and make the best use of the space. These are the results of that effort. I’m so happy with how everything turned out! Now I that I can see what we have and everything has a specific location, I won’t have strawberry containers lost in the Narnia realm of my fridge 😅 I only wish I’d done this years ago! As a mama, I’m all about making my life easier and I won’t be shamed about that. I do most of the shopping and food prep in our family and this will make my life so much easier and was worth the expense. So if this is not for you, that’s fine, but my mind will not be swayed. People shouldn’t feel shamed for curating their homes in a way that makes them happy and brings them more peace.

Ghanaian Dance sensation, Champion Rolie ,has addressed swirling rumors about his relationship with fellow dancer Afronita, setting the record straight and dispelling speculations. In an interview with popular YouTuber Kwadwo Sheldon, When directly questioned about his romantic involvement with Afronita, Rolie emphatically stated, "No, I am not dating her," during the conversation. The interview provided a platform for Rolie to share insights into his personal life and address the persistent rumors circulating on social media. Rolie expressed frustration with the negative attention surrounding his and Afronita's alleged relationship. He revealed, "If you go under my post, everything is about negative things about me and Afronita, and things don't even relate to that. People come and write all sorts of things." The interview also delved into Rolie's academic background, revealing that he attended the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST), where he completed his studies in communication design two years ago. Despite holding a certificate in the field, Rolie disclosed that he has shifted his focus entirely to dance, acknowledging unexpected financial success from his passion. He expressed gratitude, saying, "I've gotten certain pay I never expected from dancing, and I give all thanks to God." Afronita and Champion Rolie are both talented dancers and content creators in Ghana. They've gained popularity through their dance videos and collaborations on various platforms like YouTube and TikTok. While both Afronita and Champion Rolie are open about their close friendship and frequent collaborations, fans often speculate about their relationship status due to their undeniable chemistry and affectionate interactions in their videos. I’m Nick Hamman and today I’ve come to try a Gatsby from the place where the popular fast food was first invented in Athlone in the Cape Flats Area of Cape Town at a spot called Super Fisheries. The Gatsby is a simple concept: a bread roll filled with chips and a choice of fillings and sauces, but where did it originate? As legend goes in 1976 food shop owner Rashaad Pandy wanted to serve a quick but filling meal to workers helping him renovate his store. He filled a large round loaf with "slap chips" polony sausage and achaar and cut this into wedges. "Froggy", one of the workers, declared the sandwich a "Gatsby smash", alluding to the movie The Great Gatsby Known for their great fish I decided to go for the mega fish and calamari Gatsby which came together with tomatoes, lettuce, and your choice of sauce. The bread was fresh, the chips were slap, and the fish was soft and flavourful. To me, this is an excellent Gatsby, but more than that, this place deserves its flowers as a proud Cape Town institution, forever claiming its proud space in the culinary history of the area, but the question of who does it best is and should be fiercely contested, so if Athlone Super Fisheries isn’t the best, let me know where I'm going next
